snippet.textDisplay:
Sufi spin on the Sohni Mahiwal story! Sohni’s the soul desperate to reach the Divine Beloved across a raging Chenab River on a stormy, dark night. She clings to an unbaked clay pot that keeps warning her it’s doomed to fail, singing, “Kacchi meri mitti kaccha mera naam ni / Haan main na-kaam ni” (I’m unbaked clay, my name’s frail, I’m bound to fail), “Kacchiyaan da hunda kaccha anjaam ni / Eh gal ‘aam ni” (The unsound meets an unsound end / This is a truth known to all), and “Raat haneri nadi thaathaan maardi / Adiye adiye haan ni adiye” (The night’s dark, the river’s waves surge high / O dear girl, don’t be stubborn). The pot urges her to hold onto a “pakke murshad” instead: “Phad pallara phad pallara pakke murshad da / Jehda tainu paar lagaave” (Hold firmly to the true spiritual guide your “Guru” and the mantra he gives - “his word”/ Who’ll take you safely to the shore). It’s such a powerful metaphor for the Guru’s guidance leading the soul past worldly chaos as shown by a raging Chenab on a dark night !
The Sagar Veena and vocals give it depth.

snippet.textDisplay:
This song is a conversation between 'Sohni' and her unbaked pot which she mistakenly bought with her on one unfateful night to meet her lover 'Mahiwal' across chenab river, when an unbaked pot started dissolving in water and she realized that this is not the pot she used to carried on. So she begged the pot "Paar chan dy dissy kulli(hut) yar di" and the pot replied "Raat anheri nadi thathan(waves) mardi". Then the pot further let her realized that its is not the same pot she used to carried every night rather it's unbaked, so the pot said to her. " Kachi meri mitti kach mera nam ni, Han me nakam ni, kachya da honda kacha anjam ni, ay gal aam ni" then the pot further said " kachyan to rkhiye na umeed paar di" means dont put your life on me i m not able to help you😢. When the pot saw her determination towards her meeting with her lover
The pot further begged her "wekh challan(high tides) pendiyan na chaddi dil vy, ajj mahiwal nu na jana mil vy"
Means dont go today sonhi the river flow is wild today.

In the last and the most tragic line when the pot completely dissolved in water and there is no way out for her then she said to the pot that "yar nu milygi ajj lash(deadbody) yar di".
